printk() is the kernel's function for code to print messages.
it is sent to ram buffer and the system console.
dmesg shows ram buffer messages from kernel
tail -f /var/log/messages is handy
dmesg | wc -l total no. of lines.
virtual file system - proc(cd /proc) and sysfs (info is generated when you ask for that).
proc-contains lots of process info and lots more.
sys- /sys represets kernel objects,main motivation was hardware conn activity,whats connected to what,
